  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: " H. Creticus/Criticus Greek periegete, 3rd cent. BC, author of the treatise Perì tôn en têi 
    Helládi póleōn (‘On the Towns of Greece’), which describes a journey through central and northern Greece according to the following 
    scheme: distance, road and region, description of the town, local products and inhabitants....he work has usually been attributed since its first edition
    by H. Stephanus in 1589 to  Dicaearchus,  but a note in the paradoxographer Apollonius [2. 120-142 § 19] (2nd cent. BC?) attests 
    author and title."</mads:note>
